### CSS Text Align

**text-align** controls horizontal alignment of inline content.

---

### Alignment Values

```css
text-align: left;      /* Default for LTR languages */
text-align: right;     /* Default for RTL languages */
text-align: center;    /* Centered */
text-align: justify;   /* Stretched to both margins */
```

---

### text-align-left

```css
p {
  text-align: left;
}
```

Aligns text to the left edge. This is the browser default.

---

### text-align-right

```css
p {
  text-align: right;
}
```

Aligns text to the right edge. Useful for menus, quotes, or RTL content.

---

### text-align-center

```css
h1 {
  text-align: center;
}
```

Centers text horizontally. Commonly used for headings.

---

### text-align-justify

```css
p {
  text-align: justify;
}
```

Spreads words so each line has equal width. Creates clean edges on both sides.

---

### text-align-last

Controls alignment of the **last line** when text-align is justify:

```css
text-align: justify;
text-align-last: center; /* Last line centered */
```

| Value | Effect |
|-------|--------|
| `auto` | Default |
| `left` | Aligned left |
| `right` | Aligned right |
| `center` | Centered |
| `justify` | Justified |

---

### Centering Block Elements

`text-align: center` only centers **inline** content. For block elements:

```css
/* Center a div */
div {
  width: 50%;
  margin: 0 auto; /* Auto margins */
}

/* Center inline-block */
.parent {
  text-align: center;
}
.child {
  display: inline-block;
}
```

> **Key Point:** `text-align` affects inline content inside a block. Use `margin: auto` to center blocks.
